1
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:42,917
Are you open-minded?

2
00:00:43,626 --> 00:00:47,172
And that’s when he offered me
to run Vortex Global Trading.

3
00:00:47,255 --> 00:00:50,300
His import-export company based in Manila.

4
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:52,677
Chiara, I like you.

5
00:00:53,928 --> 00:00:55,472
Chiara, I love you.

6
00:01:00,226 --> 00:01:02,145
Are you sure?

7
00:01:08,485 --> 00:01:09,986
Ouch!

8
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:20,038
Very good! Amazing!

9
00:01:20,121 --> 00:01:22,165
-Great!
-Okay, okay!

10
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:25,293
Let’s all get ready
because they’re about to arrive, okay?

11
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:35,428
We need to make them feel
the warmth of our love!

12
00:01:35,512 --> 00:01:37,263
-Right!
-Right!

13
00:01:40,683 --> 00:01:42,852
-There they are. There!
-They’re here!

14
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:45,438
-Come on!
-Come on! Mikoy!

15
00:01:45,522 --> 00:01:48,024
Come on!

16
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:50,735
Wait! Mikoy! Mikoy!

17
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:52,987
There! There!

18
00:01:53,071 --> 00:01:54,697
Who's that? Show us!

19
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:56,074
Ready, count!

20
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:09,379
Where are they?

21
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,882
Oh! My son!

22
00:02:13,383 --> 00:02:15,802
What happened to you? What!

23
00:02:15,885 --> 00:02:17,971
Prague really wore you out!

24
00:02:18,054 --> 00:02:21,057
You’ve gotten thin again
from all that overtime!

25
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:23,143
Or from eating too much goulash?

26
00:02:23,226 --> 00:02:24,644
You’re exaggerating.

27
00:02:24,727 --> 00:02:28,189
Mikoy didn’t come with me.
They just sent their things with me.

28
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:31,192
I actually bike around here
all the time. It’s really fun!

29
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:32,694
See that?

30
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:35,613
That exact spot, I always crash there.

31
00:02:35,697 --> 00:02:37,282
Look!

32
00:02:37,365 --> 00:02:40,743
One, two, three. See? So many scars.

33
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:42,912
Playing in the street is fun.

34
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,706
Where are they?

35
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:46,666
They rented a motorcycle, went for a ride,

36
00:02:46,749 --> 00:02:49,377
then I noticed they stopped at a church.

37
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:51,296
What are you waiting for?

38
00:02:55,925 --> 00:02:58,761
Run! Run!

39
00:03:02,181 --> 00:03:03,600
Them?

40
00:03:08,938 --> 00:03:09,772
Hey!

41
00:03:10,481 --> 00:03:11,357
What happened?

42
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:12,442
Where are you going?

43
00:03:12,525 --> 00:03:15,570
We’re going to surprise Mikoy
at the church.

44
00:03:15,653 --> 00:03:18,907
He’s with a girl. Wanna come?

45
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:20,450
-Let’s go!
-Let’s go!

46
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:22,493
-Wait!
-Hold on! Wait!

47
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,412
-Dad! Mom!
-Mikoy!

48
00:03:24,495 --> 00:03:25,788
My son!

49
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:27,332
-My son!
-Mikoy!

50
00:03:29,834 --> 00:03:32,170
-Son!
-Dad!

51
00:03:33,588 --> 00:03:34,797
Wow!

52
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:37,550
-Hello!
-Hello!

53
00:03:37,634 --> 00:03:39,761
You're such a beautiful lady.

54
00:03:39,844 --> 00:03:42,347
Complete package

55
00:04:03,701 --> 00:04:04,535
Go!

56
00:04:11,292 --> 00:04:12,919
‎Careful. Let's go.

57
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:15,838
You're at it again, huh?

58
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:30,144
I already read your full report.

59
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:36,484
What do you think, sir? Impressive, right?

60
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:50,498
And you were even proud
to present it to the whole agency.

61
00:04:50,581 --> 00:04:53,584
I only ordered you to go to Prague

62
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:57,672
to establish a contract
with the local authorities.

63
00:04:57,755 --> 00:04:59,007
But what did you do?

64
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:01,843
You set up a surveillance mission

65
00:05:01,926 --> 00:05:04,846
without coordination
with the Czech police.

66
00:05:04,929 --> 00:05:07,432
No coordination with Interpol.

67
00:05:07,515 --> 00:05:10,560
What if you got caught?
Are you even thinking?

68
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:20,153
Just to get leverage so you could use it

69
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:31,748
Do you even realize the impact
of what you did to that kid?

70
00:05:32,373 --> 00:05:35,126
You’re going to kill me
from high blood pressure!

71
00:05:49,223 --> 00:05:50,933
Yes, sir. You're right.

72
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:52,852
I broke some rules.

73
00:05:52,935 --> 00:05:55,688
Criminals have slipped past us many times

74
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:59,192
because we keep getting delayed
following those rules and procedures.

75
00:05:59,275 --> 00:06:03,654
The law limits us to protect
the innocent who fall victim to them.

76
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:06,532
If your father could hear you now,

77
00:06:15,249 --> 00:06:20,463
And he would never compromise
his duty as a police officer

78
00:06:20,546 --> 00:06:22,215
just for a criminal!

79
00:06:27,011 --> 00:06:30,640
And I will never know what he would feel.

80
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:49,826
Bok!

81
00:06:50,868 --> 00:06:52,912
Bok!

82
00:06:55,581 --> 00:06:56,457
Bok!

83
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:59,794
You know how the General is, right?

84
00:06:59,877 --> 00:07:02,922
He’s really a bit harsh.

85
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:06,634
Actually, what he said earlier
wasn’t just a bit harsh.

86
00:07:06,717 --> 00:07:08,761
But you know that, right?

87
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:11,722
He treats us like his own children.

88
00:07:12,348 --> 00:07:15,726
That’s why he acts even more
like a father than our own dads.

89
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:19,480
He wants you back.

90
00:07:20,064 --> 00:07:22,775
He said you should talk when your head is…

91
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:24,652
cooler.

92
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:38,124
Just be the better version of yourself,
because you know what we’re up against.

93
00:07:38,207 --> 00:07:41,669
And you know how dangerous
what we’re facing is.

94
00:07:49,218 --> 00:07:52,597
I strongly feel
that they are about to make a big move.

95
00:07:57,518 --> 00:07:59,937
We’re the only ones who can stop them.

96
00:08:24,837 --> 00:08:27,757
Nice. We already have someone
we can trust in the Philippines.

97
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,175
I love it.

98
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:33,930
Wow, look at you calling me "Madam".

99
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:37,266
Come on. Take me to the mansion.
It was a long flight.

100
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:39,393
I look exhausted. I need my beauty rest.

101
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:42,230
I’ll follow you shortly.

102
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:47,527
It’s hot!

103
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:13,302
Investigate this. Vertex Global Trading.

104
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:26,482
I made sure
he won’t be able to talk against us.

105
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:30,778
How about the one
I asked you to investigate?

106
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:33,656
Here it is, sir.

107
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:35,992
That’s everything.
Nothing more, nothing less.

108
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:41,455
What did you find out about him?

109
00:09:46,627 --> 00:09:52,466
He hasn’t achieved anything in life.
Very simple. Clean record.

110
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:54,176
And honestly,

111
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:57,096
he doesn’t seem to have
anything to offer in life.

112
00:09:57,179 --> 00:09:59,265
That’s why I’m wondering

113
00:09:59,348 --> 00:10:02,268
why you’re interested in him.

114
00:10:02,351 --> 00:10:05,980
I don’t think he will be useful
for our operations.

115
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:27,668
How long have your parents been together?

116
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:34,258
Amazing, right?

117
00:10:41,057 --> 00:10:45,353
And even after so many years,
you never get tired of each other.

118
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:47,938
Your feelings for each other never change.

119
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:50,941
That’s how it should be, right?

120
00:10:51,525 --> 00:10:53,527
When you love someone.

121
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:57,073
When you love each other.

122
00:11:01,786 --> 00:11:03,245
I’m sure

123
00:11:03,329 --> 00:11:05,915
your mom and dad are like that too, right?

124
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:08,876
Oh!

125
00:11:08,959 --> 00:11:11,962
Wait, aren’t they? Do they have problems?

126
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:13,130
Not really.

127
00:11:13,214 --> 00:11:17,593
My family just has their own challenges.

128
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:20,179
Sometimes,

129
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:23,933
I wish our life was just like this.

130
00:11:24,016 --> 00:11:27,978
Simple like this. Not too complicated.

131
00:11:28,604 --> 00:11:30,147
Just happy.

132
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:36,237
Not really.

133
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:39,490
Of course, we also have
a lot of challenges.

134
00:11:39,573 --> 00:11:41,283
Yes, we’re happy.

135
00:11:42,243 --> 00:11:44,662
We can laugh about almost everything.

136
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,707
But behind all the laughter,

137
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:50,960
there are many fears too.

138
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:54,505
If one of us gets sick,

139
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:57,091
we’ll surely fall deep into debt again.

140
00:11:57,883 --> 00:11:59,427
You see,

141
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:02,972
we’re just ordinary people, Chiara.

142
00:12:05,599 --> 00:12:09,061
If people in power decide to mess with us,

143
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:12,314
we really stand no chance.

144
00:12:17,069 --> 00:12:19,530
He was found
with a significant amount of drugs.

145
00:12:20,406 --> 00:12:23,367
Enough to be considered
a drug pusher by the police.

146
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,119
That’s not true.

147
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:27,580
Because if we fight back,

148
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:32,543
we’ll end up with nothing.

149
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:36,338
You shouldn’t look down
on yourself like that.

150
00:12:36,922 --> 00:12:38,257
It’s true.

151
00:12:46,599 --> 00:12:47,516
Chiara, sorry.

152
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,435
Why are you apologizing?

153
00:12:50,269 --> 00:12:52,354
I just don’t want you to think

154
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:54,857
that I’m taking advantage of your family.

155
00:12:55,774 --> 00:12:58,027
That’s why I accepted your dad’s offer.

156
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:05,117
You’re not taking advantage
of me or my family.

157
00:13:08,537 --> 00:13:12,791
And I know you’re not doing it
just for yourself.

158
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:15,711
You’re doing it for your family.

159
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:20,758
That’s why I admire you even more.

160
00:13:22,593 --> 00:13:25,721
Maybe that’s why
I find it easy to love you.

161
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:39,109
-Hey!
-Hey.

162
00:13:40,986 --> 00:13:45,658
Can you two please
not do that lovey-dovey stuff here!

163
00:13:45,741 --> 00:13:46,867
Go inside the house.

164
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:48,619
Really? You sound like
you're encouraging them.

165
00:13:48,702 --> 00:13:50,246
All right!

166
00:14:12,226 --> 00:14:14,687
-Why did you take it off?
-Huh?

167
00:14:15,479 --> 00:14:16,522
Which one?

168
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:22,278
It’s nothing!
I don’t even know what that is.

169
00:14:28,659 --> 00:14:29,827
So this is your room?

170
00:14:31,579 --> 00:14:32,705
Yup.

171
00:14:34,498 --> 00:14:37,668
So, this is where little Mikoy

172
00:14:39,003 --> 00:14:42,339
became big…

173
00:14:42,423 --> 00:14:43,632
big Mikoy.

174
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:51,682
You should rest now,
since we had a long trip earlier.

175
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:55,477
I’m sure you’re tired already. Okay?

176
00:14:56,186 --> 00:14:57,021
I’ll go ahead.

177
00:14:59,315 --> 00:15:01,609
-You’re not going to stay with me?
-Huh?

178
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:04,069
You’re leaving me here alone?

179
00:15:06,155 --> 00:15:07,698
Yes.

180
00:15:07,781 --> 00:15:10,993
Of course, so that you’ll be comfortable.

181
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:12,870
It’s just that…

182
00:15:13,495 --> 00:15:15,581
The bed is a bit small.

183
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:17,082
Huh?

184
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:20,336
It looks like we can both fit just fine.

185
00:15:21,754 --> 00:15:24,548
-Are you sure?
-What’s the problem?

186
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:29,845
Are you not used to having
someone beside you?

187
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,640
Oh! Hey!

188
00:15:33,223 --> 00:15:34,767
No way!

189
00:15:35,517 --> 00:15:39,104
What do you think of me?
Me? Of course! I’m very used to it!

190
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:40,648
Oh really?

191
00:15:40,731 --> 00:15:44,401
Yes! With… You know…

192
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:46,403
-With?
-With…

193
00:15:46,487 --> 00:15:48,822
-With?
-With…

194
00:15:48,906 --> 00:15:51,116
With… my mom and dad.

195
00:15:52,326 --> 00:15:55,329
Then I guess there’s no problem
if we sleep beside each other.

196
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:18,352
Okay!

197
00:17:02,479 --> 00:17:03,939
Mikoy!

198
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:40,684
Where are the cucumber,
tomatoes, and carrots?

199
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:44,271
-I put them here. Where did they go?
-Oh, Auntie.

200
00:17:44,354 --> 00:17:47,441
Sorry, I used them.

201
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:49,735
Goodness!

202
00:17:49,818 --> 00:17:52,071
I thought a salad was talking!

203
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:55,032
Sorry, Auntie.

204
00:17:55,949 --> 00:17:57,910
I just needed to rejuvenate my face

205
00:17:57,993 --> 00:18:00,662
because I couldn’t
sleep properly last night.

206
00:18:00,746 --> 00:18:03,290
Hey. Why, daughter?

207
00:18:03,373 --> 00:18:05,167
What happened? Any problem?

208
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:07,169
Well…

209
00:18:31,693 --> 00:18:32,861
Ouch!

210
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:38,325
Sorry about that, okay?

211
00:18:38,408 --> 00:18:42,746
This is how Mikoy sleeps.
Even worse than a mosquito larva.

212
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:46,166
So if I were you,
I’d just break up with him.

213
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,626
Excuse me?

214
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:51,380
Just kidding! Look how you react!

215
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:54,508
Okay, what other vegetables
do you need for your face?

216
00:18:54,591 --> 00:18:57,719
Do you want okra?
Ah! Pumpkin! I have some of that—

217
00:18:57,803 --> 00:18:59,513
Auntie, no need.

218
00:18:59,596 --> 00:19:00,889
It’s okay now.

219
00:19:00,973 --> 00:19:03,225
Honestly,

220
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:05,018
I just want to…

221
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:08,438
What do you want? You know,
as long as my family can provide,

222
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:10,232
I’ll give it to you. Come here.

223
00:19:10,315 --> 00:19:13,235
Auntie, I just want to thank you.

224
00:19:20,450 --> 00:19:23,287
I’m happy to have met you all.

225
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:27,457
You know,

226
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:32,838
it’s not every day
Mikoy brings a girl home.

227
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:36,341
And since he brought you here,

228
00:19:36,425 --> 00:19:39,011
it only means one thing.

229
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:42,806
You’re important to him,

230
00:19:45,434 --> 00:19:51,523
so this house is open anytime, any season.

231
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:54,568
As long as you need a family to be with.

232
00:19:58,488 --> 00:20:01,533
Thank you very much, Auntie.
Many thanks, Auntie.

233
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:07,206
Wait, where’s that guy?

234
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:09,333
You’re alone here. Where did he go?

235
00:20:10,459 --> 00:20:12,169
Mikoy!

236
00:20:12,252 --> 00:20:13,629
Wait. Mikoy!

237
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:17,216
-Here’s your order, ma’am.
-Thank you, Mikoy!

238
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:18,967
-See you tomorrow, okay?
-Yes, ma’am!

239
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:20,219
-Just the order, ma’am.
-Okay!

240
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:21,428
-Thank you!
-Thank you!

241
00:20:21,511 --> 00:20:23,013
Sam, give me a hand.

242
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:24,348
PINAGPALA
SPECIAL BAKESHOP

243
00:20:40,697 --> 00:20:42,741
Where’s your partner? Where did he go?

244
00:20:42,824 --> 00:20:44,201
He’s on leave.

245
00:20:44,284 --> 00:20:47,788
He said he’s watching a cinema
for 12 hours straight, director’s cut.

246
00:20:47,871 --> 00:20:51,416
Wow, ha! Even longer than Lav Diaz!

247
00:20:54,670 --> 00:20:57,214
You don’t look like a cineaste.

248
00:20:57,297 --> 00:20:59,883
Even though I’m just a humble waiter,

249
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:02,010
I can still appreciate cinema.

250
00:21:02,678 --> 00:21:05,973
But honestly,
your partner is really weird.

251
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:08,183
I don’t know how you tolerate him.

252
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:10,227
You know,

253
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:13,021
Agent Sianong is very reliable.

254
00:21:13,105 --> 00:21:16,650
Don’t get annoyed, because
without him, you’d be dead by now.

255
00:21:17,818 --> 00:21:20,070
What? Right?

256
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:24,324
He convinced me not to shoot you
when I was so pissed at you.

257
00:21:34,876 --> 00:21:36,670
I want to tell you, thank you.

258
00:21:36,753 --> 00:21:40,257
I appreciate that you agreed
to help us with this mission.

259
00:21:41,717 --> 00:21:43,385
Did I have a choice?

260
00:21:44,511 --> 00:21:45,929
Still, thank you very much.

261
00:21:47,055 --> 00:21:49,766
So, what’s that? Do I get an award?

262
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:53,812
Did I win a medal of valor?

263
00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:57,065
Yes! Even better.

264
00:22:00,235 --> 00:22:03,238
Wow! Just wow!

265
00:22:03,322 --> 00:22:04,656
I think

266
00:22:05,282 --> 00:22:07,326
Agent Sianong is wrong about you.

267
00:22:08,285 --> 00:22:10,871
I think, deep inside, you want to help.

268
00:22:10,954 --> 00:22:12,497
Because you want to do what’s right.

269
00:22:16,209 --> 00:22:19,546
Look, I don’t have any report for you yet.

270
00:22:19,629 --> 00:22:21,506
I haven’t received any new information.

271
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:25,093
All I know is what we discussed before.

272
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:28,722
Viktor offered me a job at his company.

273
00:22:28,805 --> 00:22:30,057
That’s it.

274
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:32,642
I don’t know yet when I’ll start.

275
00:22:32,726 --> 00:22:34,561
Or what my position will be.

276
00:22:35,228 --> 00:22:37,147
What if they only make me
a messenger boy there, right?

277
00:22:37,731 --> 00:22:39,024
That’s how it is.

278
00:22:39,107 --> 00:22:40,984
Don’t mind that.

279
00:22:41,068 --> 00:22:42,652
The important thing is you got in.

280
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:46,698
Is anything wrong?

281
00:22:48,283 --> 00:22:50,577
Of course, I just feel guilty
towards Chiara.

282
00:22:51,411 --> 00:22:53,413
Poor Chiara, unaware.

283
00:22:54,081 --> 00:22:57,250
She did nothing but be kind to me.

284
00:22:58,502 --> 00:23:00,420
Just like I told you before.

285
00:23:01,129 --> 00:23:02,923
You are doing Chiara a favor.

286
00:23:03,507 --> 00:23:05,550
Because she was raised with lies.

287
00:23:11,389 --> 00:23:14,267
about her family.

288
00:23:15,477 --> 00:23:17,771
Love, where is Mikoy?

289
00:23:17,854 --> 00:23:20,941
Why did he leave Chiara here alone?

290
00:23:21,024 --> 00:23:24,861
No, he volunteered to deliver your cakes.
So he delivered the first batch.

291
00:23:24,945 --> 00:23:26,530
And you just let him?

292
00:23:26,613 --> 00:23:27,823
He wanted to, dear.

293
00:23:27,906 --> 00:23:29,324
Love.

294
00:23:29,407 --> 00:23:32,744
How many months has he been
working in Prague, huh?

295
00:23:32,828 --> 00:23:36,206
He just returned
and you put him to work again?

296
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:38,667
What can I do if he wants to?

297
00:23:41,461 --> 00:23:43,213
Have you talked to him yet?

298
00:23:45,340 --> 00:23:46,550
About what?

299
00:23:47,217 --> 00:23:51,596
Have you talked to him
about coming back here from Prague

300
00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:54,391
and why Chiara is with him?

301
00:23:56,393 --> 00:23:57,435
Not yet.

302
00:23:57,519 --> 00:23:59,938
Did he ask anything about you?

303
00:24:00,689 --> 00:24:03,233
Not really, but maybe you’re right.

304
00:24:03,316 --> 00:24:06,903
He might be burned out from work,
just wanting a vacation.

305
00:24:09,156 --> 00:24:11,825
Don’t hesitate to call me
if you need anything.

306
00:24:13,034 --> 00:24:14,578
I’ll wait for your call.

307
00:24:15,787 --> 00:24:18,290
As soon as you hear from Viktor,
let me know immediately.

308
00:24:18,373 --> 00:24:21,626
And if you have any new information
that we need to know,

309
00:24:21,710 --> 00:24:23,170
call me right away.

310
00:24:29,342 --> 00:24:30,677
Could something have happened?

311
00:24:30,760 --> 00:24:32,512
Like what?

312
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:33,597
Could it be

313
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:37,642
that your eldest son got Chiarra pregnant,

314
00:24:37,726 --> 00:24:40,854
so that’s why they are here to tell us?

315
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:44,691
Proposal! Darling,
maybe it’s for a proposal.

316
00:24:44,774 --> 00:24:47,694
Tess! If it really is a proposal,

317
00:24:47,777 --> 00:24:50,322
Chiara should be with her parents.

318
00:25:12,344 --> 00:25:16,014
Hello, everybody! We are
Chiara’s parents. Is Mikoy here?

319
00:25:17,224 --> 00:25:18,475
Chiara’s parents.

320
00:25:19,684 --> 00:25:22,520
That's what I'm talking about!
They're here to talk about the wedding.

321
00:25:25,732 --> 00:25:28,318
-Hello, Mom?
-Mikoy! Where are you?

322
00:25:28,401 --> 00:25:30,487
Ah. I’m just here, Mom.

323
00:25:30,570 --> 00:25:33,323
Just finishing my last deliveries.

324
00:25:33,406 --> 00:25:37,827
All right! Hurry, because
Chiara’s parents are here!

325
00:25:38,703 --> 00:25:40,080
Huh?

326
00:25:40,163 --> 00:25:42,499
Mr. and Mrs. Valtrovi?

327
00:25:43,083 --> 00:25:44,334
Is at our house?

328
00:25:44,417 --> 00:25:45,752
Yes, son!

329
00:25:45,835 --> 00:25:49,631
Donabel and Viktor just arrived!

330
00:25:49,714 --> 00:25:51,132
Don’t make them wait too long!

331
00:25:54,135 --> 00:25:55,262
All right, Mom.

332
00:26:04,437 --> 00:26:08,441
I’m really anxious
that something might happen to our child

333
00:26:08,525 --> 00:26:11,152
if he accepts that job.

334
00:26:13,530 --> 00:26:16,157
We will have to find a way
to eliminate him

335
00:26:16,241 --> 00:26:18,326
before he ruins our plans.

336
00:26:26,584 --> 00:26:29,713
We got the blessing of your mom and dad.
